nodes.name: APL support yard Entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed thru open gates and go right until you reach the bridge

nodes.name: Watson yard
nodes.additionalInfo: turn onto paved access road and park

nodes.name: 9th Street bottom entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: Turn into industry, proceed to gate on right side and enter, go straight to the end

nodes.name: 9th Street
nodes.additionalInfo: Don't stop when directions say you have arrived, proceed until you reach the railroad tracks/fence then park where it is safe to do so.

nodes.name: 25th Street - Santa Fe Ave - Near Dames and Games
nodes.additionalInfo: Turn down Santa Fe Ave toward tracks (dead end).

nodes.name: 25th street UP yard stairs
nodes.additionalInfo: Drive in and continue on the dirt past the building until you reach the stairs on the left side

nodes.name: 38 Switch by PCT
nodes.additionalInfo: Look for a walk-thru gate in the fence just west of the overpass.

nodes.name: ACTA EAST end entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: turn onto access road and follow path to the left, then follow path to the right across tracks to paved road

nodes.name: ACTA WEST end entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: turn onto access road and cross tracks when safe, then follow road to the right and proceed to the signal bridge

nodes.name: Alameda Fire House Entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: turn into access road and proceed to tracks

nodes.name: Alameda Signal Entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: turn on to access road and follow path to the right until it ends

nodes.name: Alcoa entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: Keep to the right of the gate to proceed on access road to tracks. For east end stop when you reach the tracks. For West end proceed on dirt road for 1.5 miles.

nodes.name: BNSF crossing Alameda side, Stackenol, UP tank farm
nodes.additionalInfo: turn onto watson road, cross first set of tracks then make a right onto dirt road, go straight and cross another set of tracks, continue on dirt road, go thru the open gate onto pavement and find a safe place to park.

nodes.name: Buena Park Main Line
nodes.additionalInfo: turn into gated lot

nodes.name: Buena Park YARD west end
nodes.additionalInfo: You need to drive through the warehouse parking lot and around the back of the building

nodes.name: Commerce Diesel entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: Pull up to the gate and push the button.

nodes.name: Dale Street entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed on access road to tracks

nodes.name: Dolores Entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed on access road to tracks

nodes.name: Esperanza Golf Course Crossing
nodes.additionalInfo: Be careful crossing tracks, lock gates behind you

nodes.name: Esperanza spot 1 east end entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: Go up the hill slightly and park on left.  Also, the east end of spot 1 is the west end of spot 2.

nodes.name: Esperanza spot 1 west end
nodes.additionalInfo: turn onto access road and go left up dirt road

nodes.name: Esperanza spot 2 east end entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: Turn onto access road go up slightly and park on left.  Also, the east end of spot 2 is the west end of spot 3.

nodes.name: Esperanza spot 2 west end Entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: Turn onto the access road and follow the path to the left until you reach the air station.

nodes.name: Esperanza spot 3 east end
nodes.additionalInfo: Proceed thru gates, Be careful crossing tracks, once you're across the tracks turn left and follow the dirt road until you reach the signal bridge and air boxes.  Also, the east end of spot 3 is the west end of spot 4.

nodes.name: Esperanza spot 3 Park Entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed thru gates and then right to get to the west end of spot 3

nodes.name: Esperanza spot 4 east end - Prado  Dam
nodes.additionalInfo: This will get you under the freeway

nodes.name: Esperanza spot 0 middle east gate
nodes.additionalInfo: This gate is close to the east-end of spot zero

nodes.name: Esperanza spot 0 middle gate
nodes.additionalInfo: This gate is about the middle of spot zero

nodes.name: YangMing top outside gates
nodes.additionalInfo: This is outside of the top end where we pick-up shuttle crews and drop-off ID Pool crews

nodes.name: YangMing Entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: This is the main entrance to get inside Yang Ming

nodes.name: YangMing bottom
nodes.additionalInfo: Use this when the main entrance is blocked or to get to the DP engines

nodes.name: Watson yard - Bottom, L St.
nodes.additionalInfo: turn onto dirt road and proceed next to track 20

nodes.name: TTI Track 16 gates entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed up access road then stop at bridge

nodes.name: TTI bottom, parking lot, rail tower
nodes.additionalInfo: go up dirt access road just before the parking lot and proceed to tracks

nodes.name: Santa Fe Springs
nodes.additionalInfo: enter access road from the south side of tracks

nodes.name: Rosecrans & Marquart
nodes.additionalInfo: Road Construction in this area so Navigation might not be great

nodes.name: River yard entrance top
nodes.additionalInfo: Drive in through the gates/opening toward the tracks and look for the locomotives.

nodes.name: Pier W Top Entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed up access road then straight onto dirt road, do not cross tracks under the bridge.  This is NOT the same as the TTI/Hanjin firehouse.

nodes.name: Pier F bottom, old Hiuka lead
Pier 400 Top Entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed up driveway and then to the left and into the paved lot

nodes.name: Pier 400 Bottom
nodes.additionalInfo: go in gates and park

nodes.name: Pico Yard West end
nodes.additionalInfo: go up access road

nodes.name: Pico Yard Tower
nodes.additionalInfo: Drive up the driveway that runs next to the warehouse parallel to Rosemead Blvd and you'll see the tower ahead.

nodes.name: Ocean Blvd EBCS - Tie-up/RIP tracks
nodes.additionalInfo: go in the gate and toward the tracks

nodes.name: NYK/Everport Main entrance Loading  and support yard
nodes.additionalInfo: show your TWIC to gain access then go left, across tracks then left again, thru gates, cross tracks on left then follow road to the right until it ends

nodes.name: Loop fire house
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed thru gates, by guard and to K-rail

nodes.name: Long beach yard top pier B
Long beach yard bottom pier B
Long Beach Junction
nodes.additionalInfo: this will take you under PCH

nodes.name: LAXT BNSF Tie-up tracks back  entrance
nodes.additionalInfo: follow access road to gates

nodes.name: LAXT BNSF Tie-up tracks
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed thru open gates and go right past the bridge until paved road ends then, when safe, used dirt road to go left across tracks

nodes.name: LAJ
nodes.additionalInfo: The gate opens automatically, drive straight ahead to the tall building.

nodes.name: La Mirada Yard office
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed past cement company, across tracks to railroad yard office

nodes.name: Ironsides
nodes.additionalInfo: Turn in to the dirt access road and proceed to the train.

nodes.name: Hobart Main Line West End 26th Street
Harbor Jct - Recycle plant
nodes.additionalInfo: Turn up dirt access road if safe to do so.

nodes.name: Gasper - Jackson Ave
nodes.additionalInfo: This will get you to the access road that runs between Gasper and 9th Street opposite Long Beach Pier B Yard.

nodes.name: Gasper - Edison Ave
nodes.additionalInfo: This will get you to the Edison Street WALK IN gates

nodes.name: Fullerton west end. West bound signal,  8150, 8130, 8131
Fullerton east end storage tracks 8130
nodes.additionalInfo: this will get you into the baseball field parking lot

nodes.name: Formerly Coyote Creek E/B signal
nodes.additionalInfo: Enter warehouse driveway and make a 2 immediate right turns then proceed around to rear of warehouse building, you will see the railroad access road, proceed on dirt road and go left to the train.

nodes.name: Ford building, ETD, Carman office
nodes.additionalInfo: Pick-up and drop-off ETD's

nodes.name: Firehouse, NYK and TTI
nodes.additionalInfo: proceed up driveway and to the right. For NYK follow dirt road to the right. For TTI follow dirt road to the left.
